So... hey, to steer a little clear of what I feel is a very hot room, figured I would thought of this as a bit of a cliche, me included:

Overexplanation. I know, you need all the lore and worldbuilding you can get, and that is okay, I do that all the time. I have so many details at times, I know that feeling when you started writing a few words, then it snowballed into every single little details about the bullets the guns use.

Now and then, I do feel that we can and should get away with not explaining some bits, and explain it as a "mystery / magic / exercise left to the reader." Think of it like Star Wars before the sequels (the Force, or the midicholorians). A bit of an overused example, yes, but at times, it does not have to be hard sci-fi. Add a bit of magic and mysticism into your mix! ♥
